sentences: Jesús Alfredo Merchán (born December 24, 1952)), known professionally as Chucho Merchán, is a session jazz and rock bassist and guitarist.
He received a Bachelor of Arts degree from Cambridge University in 1980.
In 1974 he traveled to England to study music at the Cambridge University.
In 1980 he received his Bachelor of Arts.
In the same year, after his graduation, he began to play double bass.
In 1983 he joined the Thomas Dolby band as a guitarist and went on his first world tour promoting the album The Flat Earth.
In 1986 he joined the band The Pretenders with whom he recorded the album Get Close.
In 1987 he joined Eurythmics on the albums Revenge, We Too Are One and Peace, and toured with the band.
He also collaborated with Eurythmics member Dave Stewart on several tracks for the Lily Was Here soundtrack, released in 1989.
